oai_dc:dc.dc:title: WAVE FORCES ON BREAKWATER ARMOUR UNITS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Juhl, Jorgen
Jensen, Ole Juul
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: wave force
breakwater
breakwater armor
armor
armor unit
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The authors have carried out a research project for investigation of the wave forces acting on breakwater armour units. The project included a literature study, hydraulic model testing and analysis of the test results. The hydraulic model testing was made in a wave flume on a 2-dimensional idealised breakwater structure with an armour layer consisting of two rows of horizontal pipes.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 22 (1990): Proceedings of 22nd Conference on Coastal Engineering, Delft, The Netherlands, 1990.
